@node "Menus" "Menus"

                                     @{u}Menus@{uu}

Project Menu
************

@{b}About...@{ub} (ShortCut: Amiga ?)
    
    Returns some basic information about Go Fetch!, including what it does, its
    current version, and the author.

@{b}About MUI...@{ub}

    Returns some basic information about your MUI system

@{b}MUI Settings@{ub}

    Allows you to configure your MUI settings, specifically for Go Fetch!

@{b}Iconify@{ub} (Shortcut: Amiga I)

    Iconifies Go Fetch! (hides the GUI) and an App Icon will appear on your
    workbench screen. To open the GUI again, double click on the App Icon.

@{b}Quit@{ub} (Shortcut: Amiga Q)

    Quits Go Fetch! and frees any resources.

@endnode

@node "Main Window" "Go Fetch! - Main Window"

                                  @{u}Main Window@{uu}

@{b}General@{ub}

1. Pressing TAB will cycle through all the gadgets. Pressing return will
activate the currently highlighted gadget.

2. Holding the mouse over a gadget for a short period of time will display a
helo bubble containing a brief description of the gadgets function.

3. Press help in Go Fetch! to display information about the currently selected
window.

@{b}The Gadgets@{ub}

@{b}Top List View - Profile List@{ub}

    This contains a list of all the profiles you have added to Go Fetch!. Only
    the basic information about each profile is shown here such as the site,
    port, file and login name.

@{b}Add Button@{ub} (Shortcut: A)

    Pressing this button will display the add window, allowing you to add a
    new profile to Go Fetch!. The new profile will be added at the bottom of
    the list.

@{b}Edit Button@{ub} (Shortcut: E)

    Allows you to edit the information for the currently selected profile in the
    profile listview.

@{b}Delete Button@{ub} (Shortcut: D)

    Pressing this button will delete the currently seleced profile. No
    confirmation action is displayed, so the effect is immediate.

@{b}Stop Button@{ub} (Shortcut: S)

    This button is normally only available in the connected state. Pressing it
    will about any transfers in operation and stop Go Fetch! from moving onto
    the next profile.

@{b}Go Button@{ub} (Shortcut: G)

    This button will tell Go Fetch! to start running through all your profiles
    and begin downloading the files. Once Go Fetch! has successfully downloaded
    a file in a profile, that profile is automatically deleted and Go Fetch!
    moves onto the next. If the file was not downloaded in the profile due to an
    error or the file was aborted, Go Fetch! does not delete the profile but
    continues onto the next one.

@{b}Quit Button@{ub} (Shortcut: Q)

    This button simply quits Go Fetch!

@{b}Bottom List View - Log@{ub}

    This displays any commands being sent to an FTP server, any messages
    received from an FTP server or any information from Go Fetch! itself.
    Information displayed from Go Fetch! itself, is in bold and
    preceeded with the hash (#) symbol.

@{b}Save Log Button@{ub} (Shortcut: V)

    Saves all the text in Log Listview as a log file with the name gofetch.log.
    A filerequester opens, asking you where you would like to save the file.

@{b}Clear Log Button@{ub} (Shortcut: C)

    Clears all the text in the Log Listview.

@endnode

@node "Add Window" "Go Fetch! - Add Window"

                                   @{u}Add Window@{uu}

@{b}General@{ub}

1. Pressing TAB will cycle through all the gadgets. Pressing return will
activate the currently highlighted gadget.

2. Holding the mouse over a gadget for a short period of time will display a
helo bubble containing a brief description of the gadgets function.

3. Press help in Go Fetch! to display information about the currently selected
window.


@{b}Site Textbox@{ub}

    The URL of the site you want to enter. This can either be a standard text
    URL such as ftp.whatever.com or the site IP address.

@{b}Add Site Button (Right Arrow)@{ub}

    Pressing this button will add the site currently in the site text box,
    into the site directory. Please note, permanent changes to the site
    directory will only be made, once the add window has been closed.

@{b}Popup Site Directory Button@{ub}

    Pressing this will display the site directory. If the site directory is
    currently displayed, pressing it again will hide the site directory. The
    site directory is intended as a covenient 'database' to add URLs which
    you commonly use to prevent you from typing them in.

@{b}Site Listview (If Displayed)@{ub}

    This displays all the URLs, currently in the site directory. Double clicking
    on any URL in the site directory will put that URL into the Site Text Box.

@{b}Delete Site from Directory Button (If Displayed, ShortCut D:)@{ub}

    Pressing this button, will delete the currently selected URL from the site
    directory. Please note, permanent changes to the sited irectory will only be
    made, once the add window has closed.

@{b}Port Textbox@{ub}

    The FTP port of the site you want to access. This is almost always 21 so you
    should have rare occasion to change it. If you don't know what this is for
    then you probably won't ever need to change it.

@{b}Username Textbox@{ub}

    The login name you need to use to log into the site, or anonymous if Anon
    Login is ticked.

@{b}Anon Login CheckMark@{ub}

    For many FTP sites, you don't need a specialised account to access their
    files because they allow anonymous login. If you don't have an account on
    the FTP site, tick this box to perform an anonymous login. Username will
    contain anonymous and password will contain the default anonymous password
    you specified as a Tool Type. This is usually your E-Mail address.

@{b}Password TextBox@{ub}

    This is the password you need to login into the site. If Anon Login is
    ticked, it will contain your default anonymous password.

@{b}Remote Path Textbox@{ub}

    This should contain the path/location of the file on the remote FTP server.
    Remember, most FTP servers are UNIX systems, so the path should be case
    correct too. For example,  /pub/system is not the same as /PUB/system .

@{b}Filename Textbox@{ub}

    This contains the complete filename of the file you wish to download.
    Remember, most FTP servers are UNIX systems, so the filename should be case
    correct. For example, gofetch.lha is not the same as GoFetch.lha .

@{b}Download Textbox@{ub}

    This contains the path where you want to download the file to.

@{b}File Icon@{ub}

    Pressing this will bring up a file requestor asking where you want to
    download files to. Once a directory has been chosen, the path will
    automatically be entered into the Download Textbox.

@{b}OK Button@{ub}

    Pressing this will add the new profile to Go Fetch!. It will appear at the
    bottom of the profile listview.

@{b}Cancel Button@{ub}

    Pressing this will discard the current profile and close the Add Window.

@endnode

@node "Edit Window" "Go Fetch! - Edit Window"

                                  @{u}Edit Window@{uu}

@{b}General@{ub}

1. Pressing TAB will cycle through all the gadgets. Pressing return will
activate the currently highlighted gadget.

2. Holding the mouse over a gadget for a short period of time will display a
